HEADWORD: Delphine
<hw>Del"phine</hw> }</mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Dauphin</er>.]</ety> <def>Pertaining to the
dauphin of France; <as>as, the <ex>Delphin</ex> classics, an edition of
the Latin classics, prepared in the reign of Louis XIV., for the use of
the dauphin (<xex>in usum Delphini</xex>).</as></def>⟦br⟧
